# NS0109 Sync Error: Failed to Login to NetSuite

If you see the error message **“NS0109 Sync Error: Failed to login to NetSuite. Please verify your admin credentials.”**, it means Expensify is unable to authenticate with NetSuite.

This error prevents reports and data from syncing between Expensify and NetSuite.

---

## Why the NS0109 Sync Error Happens

The NS0109 sync error occurs when there is an issue with the NetSuite admin credentials used to connect Expensify to NetSuite.

Common causes include:

- The NetSuite admin password was changed
- The access token was revoked or expired
- The integration credentials were updated in NetSuite but not refreshed in Expensify
- The role permissions in NetSuite were modified

When credentials are no longer valid, Expensify cannot log in to NetSuite, and syncing fails.

---

## How to Fix the NS0109 Sync Error

To resolve the NS0109 sync error, you’ll need to verify or refresh your NetSuite admin credentials.

### Step 1: Review Your NetSuite Connection Settings

Follow this guide to confirm your NetSuite admin credentials are valid:

[Connect to NetSuite](https://help.expensify.com/articles/new-expensify/connections/netsuite/Connect-To-NetSuite)

Make sure:

- The correct NetSuite admin account is being used
- The integration role has the required permissions
- The credentials match what is configured in NetSuite

---

### Step 2: Generate a New NetSuite Access Token (If Needed)

If the credentials appear correct but the error persists, generate a new access token by following Step four in this guide:

[Create NetSuite Access Tokens](https://help.expensify.com/articles/new-expensify/connections/netsuite/Connect-To-NetSuite#step-4-create-access-tokens)

After generating the new token, update the credentials in Expensify to restore the connection.

---

If you’re unsure whether the credentials were changed or need help refreshing the connection, reach out to **Concierge** in Expensify for assistance.

---

# FAQ

## Does the NS0109 Sync Error affect all exports?

Yes. If Expensify cannot log in to NetSuite, all report exports and sync activity will fail until the credentials are corrected.

## Do I need a NetSuite admin to fix the NS0109 Sync Error?

Yes. Only a NetSuite admin (or someone with the correct integration role and permissions) can verify credentials or generate a new access token.
